Brasil Foods May Expand Meat Products Plant, Valor Reports

-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 
2011-11-30T11:13:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-30/brasil-foods-may-expand-meat-products-plant-valor-reports.html
BRF-Brasil Foods SA  may expand a
meat products plant in the Brazilian state of Pernambuco “in
the near future,”  Valor Economico  reported, citing a company
official.  The plant produces 144,000 tons of sausages, mortadella and
turkey ham a year, Wilson de Mello Neto, vice president of
corporate affairs, told the Sao Paulo-based newspaper. He didn’t
give a timeframe or investment figure, Valor said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in Sao Paulo at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  